{
  "texts": [
    "Each single-exposure spectrum also has its own observation identifier (named mobsid in the LAMOST catalogs).",
    "The single-exposure spectral data can be used to analyze transient events of stars, such as stellar flares (e.g., Wu et al 2022b).",
    "In this study, we are concerned with the stellar Hα variability of steady chromosphere instead of transient events, thus the coadded spectral data of MRS are utilized in this work for their higher single-to-noise ratio than the single-exposure spectra.",
    "The observation time of a coadded spectrum is defined as the median time of multiple single-exposures, which is provided by the keyword DATE-OBS in the MRS FITS file.",
    "The MRS data used in this work are from the LAMOST Data Release 10 (DR10) foot_0, which encompasses the data from the first five years of MRS (up to June 2022)."
  ]
}